modules.description: This module implements the Salsa20 stream cipher, providing functions to create an encryption/decryption state using 16- or 32-byte keys and 8-byte nonces, and to process data using the Salsa20/20, Salsa20/12, or Salsa20/8 core functions. It operates on `Cstruct.t` values for keys, nonces, and input/output data, supporting encryption and decryption of arbitrary byte sequences. Concrete use cases include secure data transmission and file encryption where a fast, authenticated stream cipher is required.
